						<div class="postbody">Could this mean that it takes longer than the typical PPU warm up time for sprite behavior to stabilize? Hopefully someone will be able to test this properly.<br /><br />BTW, if you're using the sprite overflow to time raster effects, you may want to make the wait loop tighter in order to minimize jitter: <br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;LDA #%00100000<br />@waitForOverflow:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;BIT $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;BEQ @waitForOverflow</div></div>

