					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It wouldn't work for sprite 0?</div><br />For sprite 0 hits you can use BVC, just like you use BPL for the vblank flag. There's no need to bother setting up a mask, since BIT copied bits 7 and 6 to the N and V flags respectively, so you can just check the V flag. But if you want to keep using a generic macro, there's nothing stopping you from using %01000000 as a mask.<br /><br />One way to wait for the sprite 0 hit:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">WaitForSpriteHit:<br />&nbsp; bit $2002<br />&nbsp; bvc WaitForSpriteHit</div><br />Another way to do it, and the loop is just as fast:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; lda #%01000000<br />WaitForSpriteHit:<br />&nbsp; bit $2002<br />&nbsp; beq WaitForSpriteHit</div></div>

